Chapter 1 — Where Revenue Actually Leaks

Introduction

When a company misses its revenue target, the first instinct is usually to find one major reason.

A lost enterprise account.

A weak quarter from Sales.

Reduced marketing spend.

But after studying sales operations and building my own Revenue Leakage Detector, I realized something different.

Revenue rarely disappears because of one catastrophic failure.

It leaks through hundreds of small operational gaps that quietly compound over time.

This chapter is about understanding those gaps before trying to automate them.

The Revenue Bucket

Think of your revenue engine as a bucket.

Marketing pours in leads.

Sales works opportunities.

Customer Success drives renewals.

Everyone is doing their job.

Yet the bucket never fills.

Why?

Because dozens of invisible leaks exist throughout the revenue process.

