What Revenue Leakage Really Looks Like

Rarely:

❌ Losing one ₹50 lakh deal.

More commonly:

✓ A qualified lead waits four days before first contact.

✓ A deal sits in Discovery for 23 days.

✓ Nobody notices product usage dropping.

✓ CRM fields remain outdated.

✓ Managers discover problems only during forecast meetings.

Individually these don't seem expensive.

Collectively they become millions in lost revenue.

Why Traditional Dashboards Don't Solve This

Most dashboards answer one question:

What happened?

Revenue systems should answer a different one:

What is about to happen?

Traditional reporting is retrospective.

Revenue Operations should be predictive.

The Eight Revenue Leakage Zones

| Zone                  | What Actually Breaks                                              |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Lead Leakage          | Qualified leads never receive timely engagement.                  |
| Qualification Leakage | Sales spends time on accounts that will never buy.                |
| Pipeline Leakage      | Good opportunities lose momentum mid-funnel.                      |
| Activity Leakage      | Follow-ups and CRM updates become inconsistent.                   |
| Visibility Leakage    | Managers react after problems become visible.                     |
| Forecast Leakage      | Pipeline confidence is built on assumptions rather than evidence. |
| System Leakage        | Integrations, APIs and CRM architecture silently fail.            |
| AI Resolution         | Intelligent systems continuously monitor and reduce leakage.      |


Why I'm Building This

I'm documenting this project because I believe the future of Revenue Operations isn't about adding more dashboards.

It's about building systems that detect problems before humans notice them.

The Revenue Leakage Detector is one step in that direction.

Every chapter in this repository explores one leakage zone, explains why it happens, and shows how automation and AI can help reduce it.

